The paper proposes a multi-agent planning framework that takes into account the belief of other agents' intents and uses a learning algorithm. This suggests that the paper could belong to the sub-categories of Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI), Multi-Agent Systems (cs.MA), and Machine Learning (cs.LG). Additionally, the paper experiments with aerial robots and humans, indicating that it could also belong to the sub-categories of Robotics (cs.RO) and Systems and Control (cs.SY).
